<paragraph blockId="60.[189,1399,1028,1130]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Earlier only known by the 
<typeStatus box="[511,562,1028,1054]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
material from 
<collectingCountry box="[742,858,1028,1054]" name="Myanmar" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, Kambaiti (
<bibRefCitation author="Hippa H. &amp; van Steenis J. &amp; Mutin V. A." box="[997,1213,1028,1055]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref91629" refString="Hippa H., van Steenis J. &amp; Mutin V. A. 2015. The genus Sphegina Meigen (Diptera, Syrphidae) in a biodiversity hotspot: the thirty-six sympatric species in Kambaiti, Myanmar. Zootaxa 3954 (1): 1 - 67. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3954.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Hippa 
<emphasis box="[1079,1140,1028,1055]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). The specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[253,323,1066,1092]" name="China" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">China</collectingCountry>
fits well within the variation range exhibited by the 
<typeStatus box="[932,983,1066,1092]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
material except for the frons which is more extensively shiny and the frontal prominence which is slightly more protruding.
